.
even i created this page for this special lady, who i admire so much, by what i have learned from her - and from her steezy values for life.. ❤️😅 but the big idea what i have here, is that i want share these empowering thoughts for all of you women, and not only for her. 🧡 i think all you women deserve the supportive words & small actions, from men, to make your day. 💙 even i happen to love this one special case - i still wish other guys can view what i do, as learning path, and then implement actions seen, on their loved ones of lifetime. that way we can create collectively, together, more loving world around us. 💟 #poems #quotes #love #universe #selfawareness #metoo #lovequotes #queenofmy #earth #mindfulness #helsinki #meditation #finland #sunday #quoteoftheday #dailyquotes #tampere #turku #jyväskylä

text:
happy sunday!
.
a little sulphite info for all of you who ask me why i don’t buy dried fruit or anything with sulphites added 😷
.
those who say “oh, don’t be silly, sulphites are fine...completely safe, otherwise why would our food standards organisations & governments allow such a toxic substance in our food...” 🙈
.
don’t listen 🙉
.
it’s naive to think organisations exist for the good of our health. they don’t & probably never will. your health is your responsibility, always 💥
.
time poor parents/people: the no. 1 piece of advice to take back power:
.
✔️ flip all packaged foods to see the ingredients list.
.
some things to know:
.
👉 the first thing you see = the most used ingredient in that item.
.
👉ingredients are legally required to be listed in the order of their volume.
.
do you see sugar/salt/hydrogenated oils or any kind of corn by-product (‘high fructose corn syrup’ is a common one) as the first few things listed?
.
put. it. back. on. the. shelf.
.
👉 some healthy ingredients have long, often confusing chemical names, just like the crappy unhealthy ingredients.
.
get your phone out, take a pic, do a little online research later - or - if time permits, google on the spot... yes! at the supermarket. look around - more & more are doing this now.
.
empowering. and won’t take you long to learn the stuff you need to avoid. if anything completely stumps you - comment below, i’ll look into it 👩🏼‍🍳👩🏼‍🎓
.
👉 most foods in the health food aisle aren’t great. especially anything that ‘yells’ ✨organic✨
.
👉just because it’s organic doesn’t = a gold star. rules & regulations re: packaging claims are fuzzy, so be aware what you read on the front cover isn’t always the truth, the whole truth & nothing but the truth.
.
👉 most packaged gluten-free biscuits & breads have the worst kinds of additives in them - most likely messing with your gut. and you’re paying way too much for the privilege.
.
👉don’t feel defeated! save money & make some things yourself - aside from my gf recipes, the internet is filled with loads to try.
.
find the time. involve the kids & enjoy some great bonding, creative moments ❤️

text:
there are 42 million sexual abuse survivors living in the u.s. today, and most have never told their story. danielle mcfarlin has made it her mission to break that silence. after years spent numbing her pain with drugs and alcohol and attempting — multiple times — to end her own life, she found a reason to live and embarked on a spiritual journey. it would lead her to confront the people who hurt her and the places where her traumatic experiences happened, and to carve out her own path to empowerment and healing. now, as the #metoo movement brings more survivors and their stories out of the shadows,  @daniellemcfarlin is helping others find their path to healing from the trauma of sexual violence. over the past two months, she shared her story with producers @gatelis and @sandrawestdahl. watch the documentary tonight at 6:30 p.m. on pbs-6.
..
#survivor #courage #inspiration #empowerment #breakingthesilence #itsoktotalk #believewomen #believesurvivors #whyididntreport 
#childabuse #childabuseawareness #sexualabuse #sexualviolence #womenchangingtheworld 
#hope

text:
thank you all so much for attending and supporting the womxn in coffee event this week. it was a deeply meaningful time talking about our experiences as marginalized and underrepresented people in the coffee industry, and solutions to the problem. thank you to all the people and companies that made this happen: - host: @generalporpoisedoughnuts - event coordinator: @coldbitchbrew
- sponsors: @lamarzocco.usa , @oatly, @brandonpaulweaver of @libertybar, @frankieandjos, and @narrative.coffee - poster designer: @chairhulsizer
- panelists (as pictured): tatiana benitez, emily chavez, rowan alaka’ilenani kapanui, fabiola sanchez, molly flynn, and rhadika kapur
photo cred: @afalconstormorgreatsong 🙏i would specifically like to thank the whole general porpoise crew for generously sharing your space and for all your hard work. thank you so much to all the panelists for your vulnerability and courage. a special huge thank you to tatiana benitez for planning the whole event. you did a marvelous job. the coffee community is lucky to have you. ❤️ ✨thank you all so much for your love and support!

#️⃣ #womxnincoffee #coffeetoo #metoo #poc #pocincoffee #lgbtqia #antiharassment #antidiscrimination #workplacerights #workersrights #endtoxicworkplaces

text: i had an arabic teacher when i was eight. he used to tell me islamic stories and caress my cheek. i was too young to understand that he was doing something wrong, only that it made me uneasy. i tried my hardest to concentrate on reading the quran but i just couldn't ignore the hand rubbing my thigh. whenever i informed him of my discomfort, he would say "i'm your teacher, kanita, don't worry". and he became bolder till one day i had the courage to slap his hand away and run to my mother, crying that he made me uncomfortable. though my mother didn't realize that what i meant was he sexually harassed me, i never had to see him again. but many of us aren't as lucky to be able to stop it before a disaster happens. i hope if you've ever been mistreated, this post gives you the courage to stand up #timesup #metoo

text:
living back in the city it's so easy to lose ourselves. to forget where centre is. to feel our hearts. to feel our own love. the thought of sharing it with another somehow can be bypassed by social, work, exhaustion... and we forget why we are actually here. were it not for love, could we actually exist? so why is it given so little attention in each of our intentions, whispers, words, steps...? .
so fall in love over again and again, not with a fletting romance but with the power of love. connect with a love so deep inside you only love can surround you in every heartbeat, every breath, every lifting of your gaze as you see love manifest and unfold in front of your eyes.
.

text:
excited to present another daring writer on the speaker line-up for our “survivors, storytelling & the healing power of art” showcase on tuesday, october 23!
.
**2 days to go! get your tix now! link in bio ($15 on registration)**
.
.
samira sadeque is a new york-based bangladeshi journalist and poet focusing on migration, the refugee crisis, gender, and mental health. she began her journalism career in dhaka, bangladesh, covering the 2013 factory collapse, the country's ethnic and religious minorities, and its lgbt community. her work has appeared in reuters, al jazeera, quartz, npr, the lily, aj+, the wire.in, scroll.in, and the dhaka tribune among other publications. she is the editor of the bangladeshi identity project. her poetry has been featured at the nyc poetry festival, national book month, and award-winning platform thinking in full color, among other spaces. .
.
samira completed her m.s. in journalism from columbia journalism school in 2017. her story on childhood sexual violence in america’s south asian diaspora was nominated for a 2018 south asian journalists association award. .
.
shoutout to our sponsors @cacfnyc @iamwomankind @pondicheri for their support!
.
.

text:
|part1|
naa bheej mujhko aysy jahan main,
jahan mujhy bolny ka haq naah dya jaaye. jahan mujhy chup rehnay ka sabaq dya jaaye aur meray lafzon ko “neelaam” kya jaaye. aur agar main chup naa rahon aur kuch apni safayi main bolny ky lye aagay barhoon yaa apni raaye agay rakhon toh meri tarbiyat par ungli uthayi jaye. jahan agar main awaz uthana chahon toh mujhy baaghi bulaya jaaye, mujhy dabaya jaaye.
mujhy wahan nahi jaana jahan mera mujhpy haq naah ho magar is dunya ky kis door daraz elaqay ky ik fard ko bhi yeh ikhteyaar dya jaaye ky mujh py agar ungli uthaye toh poora zamana mujhy ruswa karay. jahan meri zuban ko band kya jaaye. aur jahan main mehaz ik “taanka” hoon. jahan mujhy kuch paison main kabhi jahez ky saath lad kar beecha jaye toh kaheen meray jism py boli lagayi jaaye. jahan sy main lout naah sakon  jahan mujhyko apny bachpan sy peerhi tak logon ky dar ko naa chahty hoye bhi dil main paalna paray. jahan mujhy dosron kee marzi par sar jhuka ky haami bharni paray bhalay hee woh meri zaat, meray pasand yaa meray mazhab ky saath ihtelaf rakhti ho. 
jahan log mujhy seekhayn ky mujhy kis tarah sy aapny aapko dhakna hai taak ky main bad-nazroon sy bach sakon, taaky meri izaat mehfooz rahay.
____________________________________

text:
la ola feminista / disidente llegó a trelew / juntas y a la izquierda, sobresaliente

más de 30.000 participantes en trelew. contra todas las maniobras burocráticas y de cobertura al poder político / clerical de la comisión organizadora, el evento fue masivo, de composición juvenil / radical y prueba de la magnitud de la revolución feminista. el colectivo nacional feminista del mst, juntas y a la izquierda, aportó el contingente organizado más numeroso del evento. y un mérito: por primera vez en el amañado acto de cierre, quedaron públicamente evidenciados dos polos antagónicos: la comisión organizadora que se niega a movilizar al corazón del poder político / clerical, y la de lxs compañerxs de juntas y el mst. destacada actuación. una prueba de coherencia consecuente.
.
.
.
.

just your friendly sunday reminder to check your privilege. as a cisgender, light-skinned asian, us citizen, college-educated, middle class, individual, i know and understand my privilege. while i am marginalized in some categories, my entire being is not constantly marginalized.
being privileged is not something to be ashamed of. profiting and benefitting from your privilege while you turn a blind eye to others suffering is shameful. awareness is your best weapon to combat the racist, sexist, classist, binary culture we live in. - diane

text:
somber post alert- looking at my black t-shirts to see what i have to wear  on #blackfridays.  on fridays i am not at work but i am going to be wearing a black t-shirt to show my support for  women who have been marginalized, victims of sexual assault, victimized by racism and all other forms of victimization and oppression.
all women i know have victimization stories and a great majority of these same women are victims of sexual assault.  1 in 3 women are sexual assaulted ( current stats)  i am not a victim of sexual assault  however i have had my fair share of experiences that come under the heading of sexual harassment -all women have.  those that say they haven’t remain unaware of what harassment is, even though it’s mandatory in the workplace that everyone is educated on these matters and they are spelled out clearly.
just last year i had an experience with a coworker that was making short innuendos toward me . i was shocked that someone who is as educated  as he is on this very topic would not know better and would be so careless.  i made a decision after he made two comments toward me that after the third comment i would report him.  the third comment never came. it was exactly around the time the #metoo movement was getting a lot of publicity ❤️. of course i wondered if that’s why he stopped. 
enough is enough and the time really is now. 
to all the men and women who read this please join forces with us and wear black on fridays to continue this forward momentum.  #metoo #oppression #violenceagainstwomen #feminists #racist #soultribe #creativepreneur #soulpreneur #solopreneur #sexualharassment #equalityforall #changeforthebetter #timesup #yoginis #socialjustice #warriorup #femaleentrepreneurs #blacktshirt #thetimeisnow #takeastand #peacefulprotest #renaesauter #sundaymotivation #therapist #lifecoachforwomen #womensrights #womenofcolor #assertiveness

text:
in the wake of #metoo movement, i was compelled to write this. 
harassment is a part of girl’s and women’s daily life; from commuting in public transport (a bus), feeling a guy forcing his penis from behind. 
to waiting on the bus stands, being a target of those lecherous eyes. 
to sitting in a local train with closed thighs, if not was that an invite? 
to being rubbed against a man’s shoulder several times, in broad daylight. 
to standing in the locals and feeling hands moving up and down your waistline. to walking in a crowded market and listening, “अरेमैडम ने बड़ी छाती फुला रखी है!”(why have you swelled up your chest? translating it to lewd comments on breasts)  what is your problem, bhai?

the stories above are so normalised that they won’t even make it a part of the #metoo movement, even if it’s about time.  if you do share, people will say, now, why? 
why do expect a woman to be rani laxmi bai, all the time? 
safe living/working/walking/breathing/talking spaces are every individual’s right.

all those women who are coming forward and sharing their stories, thank you. 
#metoo #believesurvivors #believewomen #poems #womenpoems #gender

text:
at a campaign rally in #nevada, #donaldtrump claimed #californians are "#rioting" against "#sanctuarycities" — a statement yet to be supported by evidence.
.
after deriding rep. jacky rosen (d-nev.) on her immigration policies at a rally in #elko, trump told the crowd he thought nevadians didn't care for sanctuary cities, and that californians didn't like them either. trump spoke in support of sen. dean heller, rosen's #republican opponent in the upcoming midterm election.
.
"they're rioting now," trump said of californians. "they want to get out of their sanctuary cities.".
.
but there has yet to be any evidence of rioting, especially in #california. it's unclear what specific instances, if any, trump's declaration was referring to.
.
#trumpliesabouteverything

text:
~ feminism ~
.
.
feminism is a very hostile topic because most of the people who think they are feminist doesn't have an exact idea what feminism means nor they are part of any feminist activity group to understand it. so asking a poll about feminism or sharing quotes of feminist ideology is something that budding feminists can currently offer but remember if you are a true feminist then persuade that cause till it's given a solid justification just not on a trending topic like #metoo and pusing the same ideology when another trend comes. i don't think a real feminist activist would do that.
.
recently i had a thought and i felt like sharing it here because what i feel is that women not girls, who either had a breakup or a meltdown about their age or impending marriage related topics end up being a feminist because it's easy to shut people with that word. if you say that you are a feminist then it's natural for people to think that this girl is badass and i don't think she will settle for marriage and you can keep others mouth shut for a while because c'mon, you are already a feminist now.
.
related to issues in kerala where women trying to enter sabarimala, i really don't care if anyone gets in or not. i have no problem in women entering sabarimala and seeing ayyappan but what i feel is that beyond all these issues lies an accomplishment of being the first women to overcome all the ordeals and accomplish what was forbidden. the fame will be unreal to an extend that she would be the savior for all the people who will soon follow. i presume that now more than fighting for a cause now it's a race to become the first women who battled all the odds to throw away a tradition that was defined for decades.
.
being a feminist is easy to say in social media but to step into the shoes and work for it takes a lot of courage. most of you are kids still studying so just study for the time being don't worry this becau by the time you are good enough to understand the topic, you can still find trending topics to fight for. go women power!! .
.
.
.
#stopitvishnu #falsebeing #feminism #sabarimalaverdict .
.
.

text:
there are days when i won't even get up..
not to eat..or wash...
not even to go open the door to let my cats come into the room and comfort me..
i just stay there..in the once comforting bedroom that i turned into my prison..
my world of depression
staring at those white walls, this white ceiling
crying without making a single noise
because if i let even one tiny sob get out i will break
i can spend days at a time like this
and it's torture. pure and simple torture
i wish i could get up
i wish i could scream
i wish i could walk this one meter to my door and hug my cats...
the pain is just paralyzing.

this is one of the numerous days when i must remind myself to stay strong.

those picture (baby gimli) are really comforting for me to stare at so this is why they are with this post.

#metoo #mentalhealthawareness  #animallovers #staystrong

text:
the ever-so-amazing bartender – pippa guy – who’s added a fierce energy, grace and softness to the award-winning american bar at the savoy hotel.
.
i’m just getting to know pippa – we’ve met a couple of times. pippa is just heading into her 6th year as a bartender, and she firmly believes that “you get out what you put in – there are so many people that work incredibly hard, but there’s not enough support and appreciation towards everyone’s dedication.” over the next three years, pippa hopes to see the industry become even more conscious of our impact on the environment. she’s hoping that each of us will take more of a leading role in this cause – how do we look after “waste”, what is “waste” and how do we manage the world around us? when it comes to the drinks industry, and when it comes to making a difference, pippa’s advice is simple “stop doubting yourself”. pippa’s journey at the savoy is ear marked by a figure she would love to chat with – ada coleman – the first and only female head bartender at the american bar. “from the records we have, ada seems to be a pretty fiery character, but also took quite a lot of unpleasant treatment in her position. i'd love to buy her a martini and listen to her stories. she’s ultra-inspiring.” .
beyond the savoy, pippa desperately wants to spend some time in california – after all, her mum was born there, and craves some family and beach time! if pippa wasn’t bartending, she’d most likely something to do within the science, sport or travel industries; “i've always thought i'd really enjoy marine biology, the problem is, i'd be awful at sitting behind a desk for long periods of time – how can people get anything done sitting in one spot for so long?!” the perfect moment for a cocktail? “i’m a complete sun worshiper, so after a long day in the sun, just towards sunset, somewhere outside with a good view, i’m drinking a gin & tonic.” .
pippa’s one line that describes her, “there is freedom waiting for you, on the breezes of the sky, and you ask ‘what if i fall?’ oh but my darling, what if you fly?” wise words from erin hanson. #minibarleadingladies

text:
those who have experienced sexual abuse as children and adolescents have an above-average prevalence of psychological symptoms later in life. their general sense of wellbeing is affected, and compared with people who have not been abused they suffer more frequently from:

post-traumatic stress disorders
somatization disorders
eating disorders (especially bulimia nervosa)
alcohol, drug, and medication abuse
depression
borderline disorders
suicidal behavior.

text:
//in light of #mentalhealthawareness awareness and #metoo//
part 1

think of mouths for a second. the way lips curve around while forming words, jaws moving in synchronization, and that slight flash of teeth and tongue when you say the word, "yes." now think of how that happens. of the signals the brain sends out like a remote control with millions of switches, and how they form first a thought, then a confirmation, before they are translated into words. 
imagine. just for a second, that this remote control wasn't fully in your control. brainwashing? perhaps. but there are other words for it. 
you see, my story wasn't a dark alley in the middle of the night, wasn't a man looking at me in a way that told me that i needed to run. it was love, folded into the bedsheets and the way my fingers glided over skin. it was the voice in my head screaming at me to stop.  it was a woman, my best friend. who never would have asked me to do what i did. 
a woman, glorious in her resistance, who had first hand experience of how bad it can get. a woman who i had loved. and who loved me. who i'm still friends with and was agonized when i told her about it later. but i didn't know how to say no. 
not to tied hands on bedframes, or to lying on top. not to things to say, ways to touch, people to be. not to anything at all. because it was all supposed to be natural? wasn't it? 
we are taught that sex is natural. that to love someone is to want to touch them in ways you don't touch another person. but to me. to a graysexual, bipolar, traumatized woman who had stood in between fights for years, who had tried to help even when she couldn't, it was torture. torture because yes, it was natural.
natural to do things i didn't want to do. natural to feel as if i didn't deserve pleasure. natural to put others above myself, even in an act which is supposed to be a portrayal of togetherness. 
as a queer, graysexual woman, as a sufferer of mental illness, as someone who has loved and been loved before, here is a story not about the consent we give to others, but to ourselves. because sometimes, our mouths are tied to invisible strings and stretched and stretched apart.

text:
//in light of #mentalhealthawareness
and #metoo// part 2

and we say yes but it isn't us saying it. it's a woman who doesn't think she has the right to say no. mental illness telling us our only worth is how we help others. society sexualizing love until we think that it cannot exist without it. 
because you should never have to do something if some part of you doesn't want to, no matter who says you do. even if that person is only yourself. 
when a boy called me, a few nights ago to ask me if i had been uncomfortable, to apologize for saying something he thought was insensitive, i realized that i had never thought that being comfortable was something i was entitled to. and it was that realization which led me to finally stop battling with myself about the binary nature of feminism. because to work to rid the world of binaries, it is first essential to realize what the binary causes. the way women are led to believe that they do not have a right to say no. the way men are led to believe that they must be strong. and how sex assigned at birth is simply used to lump us into an understandable category in this rotting hell that is this structure. 
it is today, after years of denying myself happiness, of denying myself the right to say no, that i can finally call myself a proud, feminist.

text:
👋🏼 october is domestic violence month, if your in the kansas city area i would love to see your face at the free seminar focused on healing and empowerment at @warriorsacademykc⁣⁣ oct 27 1-4!
⁣⁣
the free seminar will have multiple speakers covering topics such as spotting early signs of domestic abuse, and much more. there will also be a hands on portion led by @frosst13 a black rank in krav maga.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
nearly 20 people per minute are physically abused by a intimate partner in the u.s our overall goal is to help raise public awareness and stop this cycle. this event is sponsored by @warriorsfuelfood @warriortacticaltraining @nutrithority @warriorsacademykc and we will have giveaways from a few others such as but not limited to @chromesupps_bosslady a big thank you to them for this shirt.  message myself or @thugwithphd for more info! ⁣

text:
heartbroken!!!! busy phillips, you broke my heart open. and then you mended it. and thank you, thank you, thank you, thank you. ⁣
⁣
i admire and respect you and have a lot of love for you in my heart. ⁣
⁣
and not that you would, but if you ever find yourself wanting or needing anything from me - i’m here for you, busy! ⁣
⁣
if you’re a woman, busy’s new book is a must read. if you’re a man, busy’s new book is a must read. for goodness sake, whoever you are just read it! ⁣
⁣
i stayed up all night, breathing in page after page. burst into happy, grateful, desperately sad, long-trapped tears. found hope. found that feeling i needed to be ready to try again. ⁣and we all need that. we all need it, you guys! ⁣
and i mean, this book comes with its own playlist. come on, y’all. that’s amazing! ⁣
⁣
thank you, busy. thank you. thank you. thank you. ⁣
⁣
#metoo #readbooks #busyphillips #thiswillonlyhurtalittle #love #hope #yesyoucan @busyphilipps @touchstonebooks

text:
hello friends,
 मेरा नाम मुख्तार अली है। मैं एक विद्यार्थि हूँ। इस देश और दुनिया में me too की जंग की लहर दौड़ रही है। ये कुछ मामलो में सही है परन्तु आज जब किसी एक ने आवाज़ दी तो औरो के भी कई अफ़साने निकल कर सामने आते हैं। कई सालों की घटनाएं आज याद आती हैं क्यु?
इससे पहले ये घटनाएं उनके तक सीमित थी परन्तु अब नहीं हैं। आखिर क्यों लोग करते हैं। सब ठीक है माना कि आप के साथ गलत हूआ है जब गलत हुआ तो अपने अपनी आवाज़ बुलंद क्यु नही की?
मैं इस बात से कफ़ा हूँ की  me too के द्वारा लगाये गये आरोपियों में से मैं एक को अपना आदर्श और मनता था कारण मैं उनके भाषण से प्रवाहित था। जब आज उनके गलत कार्यो के बारे में सोचता हूँ तो मेरे सामने अधेरा छा जाता हैं। जिन को मैंने अपना आदर्श माना वे दुष्कर्मि निकले। इसमे मेरी कोई गलती नहीं है। और जो लोग फालतू की बकवास me too पर डाल रहे हैं वे फालतू की पोस्ट ना डाले। इस दूनियाँ मे कई लोगों की बकवास पसंद नहीं मैं कुछ कर पाया नही ना तो मेरे इस एक पोस्ट से क्या होगा। खैर मेरी यही दुआ है कि मेरे देश उन्नतिशील हो विकास हो लोग होशियार हो और अकल्मंद हो। जय हिंद जय भारत

मैं इस बात से कफ़ा हूँ की  me too के द्वारा लगाये गये आरोपियों में से मैं एक को अपना आदर्श और मनता था कारण मैं उनके भाषण से प्रवाहित था। जब आज उनके गलत कार्यो के बारे में सोचता हूँ तो मेरे सामने अधेरा छा जाता हैं। जिन को मैंने अपना आदर्श माना वे दुष्कर्मि निकले। इसमे मेरी कोई गलती नहीं है। और जो लोग फालतू की बकवास me too पर डाल रहे हैं वे फालतू की पोस्ट ना डाले। इस दूनियाँ मे कई लोगों की बकवास पसंद नहीं मैं कुछ कर पाया नही ना तो मेरे इस एक पोस्ट से क्या होगा। खैर मेरी यही दुआ है कि मेरे देश उन्नतिशील हो विकास हो लोग होशियार हो और अकल्मंद हो। जय हिंद जय भारत

text:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if you’re waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isn’t forthcoming. what most of them haven’t lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it. 
#nomore #adamcroasdell #eccarius #ignisscientia #lordbothwell #actor #voiceactor #ffxv #preacher #reign #vampire #supernatural #losangeles #women #supportwomen #timesup

twitter @acroasdell

-
-

text:
inte en dag för tidigt. #metoo gav fler kvinnor och barn (även män) modet att anmäla. det gav hopp om förändring och om rättvisa. men i verkligheten fortsätter sexualbrotten att prioriteras bort. brott mot kvinnor och barn har fortfarande låg status. och det säger sig själv att poliser som saknar den kompetens som krävs för att på ett korrekt sätt hantera en sexualbrottsanmälan, inte kan göra ett så bra jobb som de säkert önskar.
hur många anmälningar är helt förgäves? över 22 000 sexualbrottsanmälningar under 2017 men endast 1 162 lagföringsbeslut. bara en av tio polisanmälningar om våldtäkt ledde till åtal. det siffrorna talar för sig själv. hur många av de 22 000 anmälningarna dör redan vid anmälningstillfället?
ge alla poliser som arbetar med sexualbrott förutsättningar att göra ett bra jobb för de brottsoffer som orkar och vågar anmäla. med rätt bemötande och mer rättssäkra förundersökningar kommer fler utsatta att våga anmäla sina förövare. mörkertalet är stort. i dag är det enligt brås ntu* endast 15 % av dem som uppger att de har varit utsatt för ett sexualbrott som anmäler. 15 %. hundratusentals brottslingar kommer undan utan att ens anmälas. insikten svindlar. 
#rävsaxen #sexualbrott #våldtäkt #kvinnovåld #kvinnoliv #mänsvåldmotkvinnor #barnrätt #brott #polisen

text:
בא לי להקיא ממנו. בא לי להקיא ממנה שהיא מצדיקה גברים מסוגו. אין לי אפילו איך לנסח את הפוסט הזה. בפרט ששמעתי באוזניי ממנכ"ל בכיר שמנכ"לים נמנעים בימים אלו מלגייס נשים או להיות עם נשים בחדרים ומדירים אותן מהחשש לתלונה. 
יש לי רק דבר אחד להגיד לגברים האלה: מי שלא אנס ולא מטריד לא צריך להיות מוטרד מהעניינים האלה. 
נשים לא מחפשות להמציא סיפורים כדי להיות בטרנד. הן פאקינג מוטרדות על בסיס יומי. ולא צריכות להיות עכשיו גם מודרות בגלל שחלקכם לא יכולים לשמור את הזין שלכם בתוך התחתונים #metoo

text:
i went to agra in july and the first place i went to see was the agra fort. according to the guide, akbar used red sandstone to restore the ruined fort to its glory and shah jahan destroyed some parts of it to use white marble in place. he had quite an obsession with white marble.. obviously!

it's the same place shah jahan was locked up by his son and was forced to watch the mausoleum he built in the memory of his wife from afar. he could see the entire world but could only do that from a small window. the love of his life, his dreams to build another taj in black, all of it was locked up with him.

imagine being in shackles when the world and everything in it is just right in front of you.
imagine being snatched of whatever you've built with your hard work by someone who neither respects you or your feelings.

that's how women all over the world feel at one point in life.

the world is big and yet we are restricted by societal norms. the fear of being violated, of being harassed, degraded, deprived of respect and appreciation; the hatred faced by a male chauvinist who can't get over the fact that a woman is better at the job than him, the constant nagging about being weak and powerless that messes up with confidence and self respect...all of it is just like being imprisoned and watching the world from a tiny window.

but unlike shah jahan, the women haven't accepted it as their fate. 
with each #metoo post,with each person standing up for normalising conversations about periods, each protests in favour of pro-choice,each voice standing up for equal pay,each adult educating their child about consent and each woman standing up against her assaulter despite facing injustice and backlash and humiliation, the shackles have begun to wear down.

with slow, steady steps we are going to break free and get away from the imprisoned state
because the world is too big and too beautiful to just see from a window and nobody ever has the right to say otherwise! 
#agrafort #uttarpradesh_ig #sundaypost #shetravels #thoughts #prochoice #agra #mughalarchitecture  #feminist #travelindia #optimism #travelwithme #worldnomads #moments  #mykindacity #incredibleindia  #uttarpradesh

name: 이현학
pre_proc_tweet:
의 지목으로 뜻깊은 일에 참여합니다. 학생들의 용감한 목소리에 귀기울이고 함께 연대합니다. 우리의 '불편함'이 예민한 것이 아니고 당연해질 때까지 함께할 것입니다.

 
 
 
1.   해시태그와 함께 자신의 연대문장을 적는다.
2. 인증사진을 찍는다.

text:
لیدی گاگا: قدرت را پس گرفتم
..
مجله elle مراسمی برای تقدیر از زنان هالیوود برگزار کرد که لباس مردانه و سایز #بزرگ لیدی #گاگا در #فرش_قرمز این مراسم حسابی توجهات را جلب نمود.

لیدی گاگا در این مراسم یک سخنرانی احساسی داشت که شنونده ها را حسابی منقلب کرد. قسمت هایی از این سخنرانی زیبا را در ادامه می خوانید:

امروز وقتی داشتم برای این مراسم آماده می شدم، لباس های زیادی را امتحان کردم. کفش های پاشنه بلند یکی پس از دیگری، جواهرات، لباس هایی از زیباترین ابریشم های جهان و پارچه هایی گران قیمت اما صادقانه بگویم، در دلم حسی از درد داشتم و از خود پرسیدم اینها واقعا معنای زن در هالیوود هستند؟

ما فقط اشیایی برای سرگرمی دنیا نیستیم. ما به سادگی تصاویری نیستیم که فقط اشک و لبخند به صورت مردم بیاوریم. ما اعضای یک گروه بزرگ زیبایی نیستیم که فقط برای لذت بردن عموم مردم در برابر دید دیگران قرار بگیریم. ما زنانی در هالیوود هستیم. ما صداها هستیم. ما افکار و عقاید عمیق و عقلانی ارزشمندی در مورد جهان داریم و ما قدرت صحبت کردن و شنیده شدن داریم و هنگامی که ما را خفه کنید به مبارزه خواهیم پرداخت.

بنابراین من بعد از امتحان کردن بیش از ۱۰ مدل لباس، با احساس غمی عمیق در قلبم که چرا تنها مساله مهم در این فرش قرمز این است که چی بپوشم، یک کت و شلوار سایز بزرگ از برند مارک جیکوبز را در گوشه اتاق دیدم و همان را انتخاب کردم. اطرافیانم لباس و برندهای دیگر را پیشنهاد می دادند و من به این فکر می کردم چرا همه دغدغه آنها به لباس معطوف شده است. اما من یک کت و شلوار بزرگ مردانه نه یک لباس شب شیک و #زنانه را انتخاب کردم و سپس شروع به گریه کردن نمودم.

امروز من در این کت و شلوار خودم را حس کردم. در این کت و شلوار من احساس حقیقی درونم را بسیار خوب حس کردم و بعد از آن چیزی که می خواستم در سخنرانی امشبم بگویم برایم روشن شد.

من به عنوان یک بازمانده آزار #جنسی که هنوز آنقدر شجاع نیست تا اسم آن مرد را به زبان بیاورد تصمیم گرفتم قدرت را پس بگیرم. به عنوان یکی از بازماندگان آزار جنسی توسط کسی در صنعت سرگرمی، به عنوان یک زن که هنوز آنقدر شجاع نیست تا اسم او را بگوید، به عنوان یک زن که با درد مزمن زندگی می کند، به عنوان یک زن که در سن بسیار کم مجبور بودم به چیزی گوش دهم که مردها به من می گفتند، امروز بالاخره تصمیم گرفتم که قدرت را پس بگیرم. امروز من شلوار می پوشم.
#metoo
#زن_نوين 
#لیدی_گاگا
#زنان_مدرن_جهان
#زنان_اندیشمند
@hamrato4women

text:
no means no,  a dare to be taken by every woman. 
i would like to say that let's not tolerate any more harassment. let's not stay silent anymore. let's take a stand at the moment. let's say no means no before you say me too. let's not become a victim again. 
p. s: it's just my opinion regarding the metoo campaign 
all my experience, i feel that in most of the cases a rigid rejection & an active guts from your side don't make the situation worse. 
so just wanted to share a bit of confidence to all the girls out there to say no means no before you have to say me too. 
thank you❤
#metoo #metoocampaign
#wewoman #woman #india #indian

text:
the first #passionpreview comes from @feistyfletch, curator of passion preview: “for the last 6 years, social media has been my passion! i started looking to the internet because i wasn't feeling accepted by the people surrounding me irl. with social media, i was able to learn more about lgbt culture, find new passions, and make friends from around the world!”
-
why social media? “there is so much potential with social media! social media keeps us digitally connected in a world that sometimes feels like it's falling apart. movements like #metoo prove that digital spaces can cause major change. also, social media is so fun -- you can create whatever you want!”
-
to someone that doesn’t like it: “i get it. with all of the different data issues and recent news, i understand why you wouldn't enjoy it. but just remember, social media is what you make of it! you can follow and create community in whatever way you want.”
-
to someone interested in social media: “what are you waiting for?? get started! figure out a username you can use across social channels and start making content. find others that have the same interests as you, follow them, and share each other's content! have fun, be careful, and ignore the haters!”
-
passion emoji: 👨‍💻
-
want to pass on your passion? just take the 5-minute google survey in our bio!

text:
[📚 #bibliotheque2p, le livre de la semaine] les histoires d’amour adolescentes racontées dans la fiction sont souvent à double tranchant. si celles-ci sont bien écrites, on peut y dénicher quelque chose de salutaire, voire de nécessaire. dans le cas contraire, on se retrouve à subir la série « 13 reasons why » (déso pas déso). le roman « tous nos jours parfaits » de jennifer niven fait partie de ces récits à la fois bénéfiques et éducatifs. elle nous raconte la passion de violet et finch, deux ados en proie à la dureté de l’existence qui finissent par se trouver alors qu’il et elle sont – quasi littéralement – au bord du gouffre. à travers son livre, l’autrice veut surtout nous parler de santé mentale et de suicide, et de la stigmatisation qui entoure les deux. le but n’est pas simplement de dépeindre la romance tortueuse de deux ados en pleine crise existentielle, non. « tous nos jours parfaits » va plus loin. finch souffre d’un trouble bipolaire, et cela nous est d’abord montré avant d’être nommé. c’est un jeune homme qui cherche toujours les mots pour décrire la vie, mais qui refuse d’en mettre sur son mal-être. de son côté, violet a perdu sa sœur aînée dans un accident de voiture et ne sait pas comment continuer à vivre « normalement ». elle aussi a perdu les mots, qui étaient pourtant sa première source de catharsis. c’est ce même sentiment d’impuissance et de détresse qui les réunira et les conduira sur les routes de leur psyché, autant que sur celles de l’indiana. avant de commencer ce bouquin, l’on s’attend à plonger dans le marasme des considérations adolescentes, qui constituent la base d’une majorité de fictions young adults. mais en fin de compte, on en ressort bouleversé-e, tant la sincérité de l’écriture est inéluctable.
🗞 http://bit.ly/revuedepresse79
➡️ lien en bio !

text:
it has been a week of 'letting go'. it has been a week of denial and acceptance -- a painful journey was made as one story was released from its silence, finally. the few steps i took towards the middle to stand and say my story  aloud, has freed me today. silences take time to heal. i have lived in shame, blaming myself for the incident for years. no one told me that it wasn't my fault, i had to say that to myself.  it's important to voice these stories and share them because there are many more like us, out there, and there's strength in solidarity. it's important to know that you're not alone, and that it will all be okay. . 
sending all of you out there hope & strength !

text:
माथे पर स्वर्णिम चंद्र सजा,
और अधरों पर मुस्कान लिए,
ले रक्त-लालिमा गालों पे,
है लब पर मधुरिम गान लिए,

वह निशा-दिवस सब एक मान,
#गौरव वह कर में प्राण लिए,
है मानवता का श्रेष्ठ रूप,
वो जिये चक्षु में शान लिए.. जो स्नेह की ज़िंदा मूरत है,
है ममता का पैगाम लिए..
नित सृजन विश्व का करने को,
आतुर है निज बलिदान लिए,

ज्यों दिव्य किरण वह बिखरा दे,,
त्यों मृत उठ जाए प्राण लिए,
जो है देवी का जीवित रूप,
जो है सब का संज्ञान लिए,

है महाविदुषि नारी वो,
होंठों पे जग का ज्ञान लिए..
है प्रेम की अविरल धारा जो,
देखो उसको सम्मान लिए.. है  विनती बस इतनी,
सुन ले जग एक पल ध्यान लिए,
जीने दोे उसे जो आई है,
खुद सृष्टि का निर्माण लिए.. जीने दोे उसे जो आई है,
खुद सृष्टि का निर्माण लिए... let's come together for a society where there is no more need of a movement like #metoo

text:
living life without numbing myself is new to me... and it's very scary. i finally wrote my own #metoo story down and shared it with my sisters, which resulted in a very painful, very sober and very feeling sort of day. i'm damn near 30 and am finally addressing what happened to me from when i was in diapers until i was six years old. i'm not protecting anyone by hiding my feelings or my story anymore. the bitch is back, folks, and i'm here burning brighter than ever. 
#feeling #sober #sobriety #numb #runningdoesnthelp #childhoodtrauma #sexualabuse #callitlikeitis #fuckthepeace

text:
when we think about sexual harassment/abuse, what comes to our minds is the image of a man forcing himself on to a woman. this is one of the most harshest forms of sexual abuse. there are some forms however which get unnoticed as 'boys will be boys.' sexual harassment occurs also when a man says 'mashaallah' when you walk down the street. sexual harassment is when a guy brushes his hand "accidentally" on your. sexual harassment is when you get commented on why you're wearing ripped jeans. it occurs when the x-ray vision of men scan you from head to toe. and it is because we stay silent during these 'petty issues' that women today get raped on the streets, in their offices and even in their homes. think about it. you speaking up can save someone else. 
#metoo #sexualharassment #sexabuse #force #boyswillbeboys #likeforlikes #followforfollowback #liferealitytruth #lifegoals #speakup #sexualpredatorsshouldbejailed

text:
i coach men as well as women and they suffer just as much as we do when they are faced with relationship break ups, death of a loved one, divorce, moving, financial stresses, health issues etc.😪
most of my clients (women and men) are over 50 and find themselves alone after being married for a long time, raising children, moving out of the family home, separating assets and dating with the hopes of meeting that special one.
although, i can share the sentiments of  strong and courageous women in the #metoo movement, men suffer as well.
i urge both genders not to bring the same traits and behaviors that were unhealthy and unconscious to their new relationships. being set in your ways doesn't bode well with new people.
hopefully, we learn and grow from what didn't work to what works better.
and, if you are using online dating to find your match, remember it takes approximately 100 hours of eye to eye physical contact to really know someone. friendship first. chemistry's great but there is a virtual candy store online of both men and women to choose from. friendship lasts much longer and can turn into true love faster than chemistry ever can.
be authentic above all else. be adaptable. be curious. be a loving and caring person who brings calm and peace...respect yourself and each other.
blessed sunday 💖

text:
#metoo: actor uday chopra steps down from sofa after no allegations surfaced against him

after spending hours vegging out on his sofa daily, “actor” uday chopra finally stepped down from his couch on saturday after no allegations under the metoo movement were directed against him. it is revealed that uday took this serious step only to promote the idea of voluntarily accepting that men are always wrong and that all men are trash.

in a recent viral post, a blogger drew attention to the fact that every woman has been harassed at least once in her life, however, not a single man has ever accepted harassing any woman, which frankly does not add up. taking note of this many feminists and math enthusiasts were later seen vouching for the fact that all men are indeed trash.

following this, the #allmenaretrash became a mightier mass movement than metoo and saw many famous personalities stepping down from their position. accomplished “actor” uday chopra, who currently holds only one position i.e. on his sofa, has decided to step down from it. uday chopra has not only set a precedent for men all across the globe but has also managed to move several others who usually lie on their sofa or bed all day long.

text:
from the kind of sexual harassment they are facing to the bitterness in their relationships with men, for the first time ever, actresses, women technicians and those working in other departments and even women journalists from telugu film industry have a platform now to speak out and raise their voice against what is happening with them.

voice of women(vow) is a team of five women nandini reddy, jhansi, swapna dutt, supriya yarlagadda and suma kanakala. the collective effort of these five daring and dynamic women is the vow.

in context to the #metoo movement has taken the internet by storm with so many sad stories of sexual harassment coming to light every day, in small team has welcomed complaints from women in the industry. "touching, ogling and other kinds of harassment in the industry have now become common only because the predators think that the victims are accepting it by remaining silent. victims did not have a platform to speak out. but now, one need not be afraid to speak as we are here to listen to you," said jhansi.

while these people are going to take strict actions against the predators, details of the victims are going be kept highly confidential. there is a special committee of members who will be deciding on the action that has to be taken. "we want to tell all the women out there that there is no need to worry anymore as we are ready to listen to what you are going through. what is happening with you is completely unacceptable," said one member, with request to anonymity.

at the same time, she also made it clear that being in relationship and then accusing the man on harassing her sexually is completely unaccepted here. "you should agree that you were in a relationship and that it has become bitter now. if you want to walk out of it now, leave it to us and we shall take care," she added.

as per vishakha guidelines, a cash (committee against sexual harassment) is formed and the members of the panel will the necessary action. this panel will ensure that all that they do contributes to healing, transparency and accountability.

#voice of women's.

text:
actor meira omar alleges @anirbanblah sexually assaulted her.
.
omar said that he called her to his work space which was actually an apartment in juhu, mumbai where he stayed away from his family. blah asked her to let her hair down and feel comfortable. they chatted for the night where he told her, “how he is a man who can get girls to come out of their shell, bring out their inner sexiness and awaken other desires in men.”
.
the report says he even went ahead and told her about a specific case where a girl reached out to him and she was gorgeous, but too timid and shy. so he locked her in his balcony in that same juhu apartment, where we were sitting and forced her to masturbate. .
"he narrated the story to me with a sense of pride. he showed me pictures of the girl he was currently working on, pointing out the difference between before he discovered her, and after he did.”, said omar
.

text:
our coming campaign will be focused on child abuse. so just how bad is the issue of child abuse in the united states?
•
•
•
every year more than 3.6 million referrals are made to child protection agencies involving more than 6.6 million children (a referral can include multiple children).
•
•
the united states has one of the worst records among industrialized nations – losing on average between four and seven children every day to child abuse and neglect. •
•
a report of child abuse is made every ten seconds. 😢

•
•

text: "a smile on my face doesn't mean that my life is perfect it means i'm grateful for what god has blessed me with." a few months ago i wouldn't of been able to say the same thing. mental health is so important to talk about. it's something that can be helped with the right recourses. i cannot afford to talk with a specialist about the things i've been through in life but here are some other  things that have helped me: 1.) following my gut: and saying no to things that are the "safest route" but you know aren't going to make you happy. 2.) eating healthy and exercising i don't do it to have a "perfect body" it's good for my brain, my heart, my lungs. 4.) sleep 😴: your body needs rest to be stronger and healthier both physically and mentally. 5.) reading 📖: when i read it clears thing up for me a lot. it's so good for your mental health. it helps me to have great ideas to stick with them and see where they go. it helps me think that i can.  my dreams are still a possibility in this life. i learn and i keep learning. same thing goes for writing. 5.) my mom and good friends: my mom has given so much for me and my siblings. she is the strongest person i know and the most loving caring person. i'm currently not living with her anymore because i have to think of my mental health as a priority with that growing on my own and she has helped me and guided me so much to the right path. i love her so much and i miss her like crazy but facetime and talking on the phone helps a lot with that. no matter how far away she is i always have her in my heart with every decision i make in life. she's my, " what would she do". friends: people who have things to say in this life. people who help you stay happy. people who will listen to you and give an honest opinion on the situation. most of all people who love you for who you are and more. ♥️. stay strong and look at yourself in the mirror and say: you are a badass. you are beautiful, kind, important in this world 🌎. #mentalhealth #reading #eatinghealthy #healthyfood #health #healthylifestyle #exercise #family #art #smile #music #life #growingup #metoo #learning #love #friends #truefriends #bond #talk #dontgiveup #you #staystrong

text:
they told me have faith in god. i did, i do, but this anxiety i feel still cripples me. they say i don’t pray enough, but i do, my knees bent all night weeping, praying that this sadness and emptiness doesn’t consume me. they say “this too shall pass”, but it isn’t, it’s been days, turned weeks and months and each day i want to end it all. 
how hard is it for people to just listen? to empathize? i know i need a therapist, but i fear my faith in god would be questioned. wouldn’t it be nice if they encouraged me to get one? no one told my husband to pray when he cried about severe pains around his abdomen. but this pain in my heart, they say to pray away.

text:
i had to leave my job because i was so uncomfortable every time i had to work on a project with those men or go to the warehouse. i was blamed for being “too assertive” & “too flirtatious.”
.

my ex told me i “should change my approach.” my female boss didn’t believe me either. my parents blamed me for “quitting another job.” .

yes, i still care for him & we are friendly, but he won’t remember & realize any of it until he reads this post. he doesn’t know how deeply he hurt me for taking the side of their “long term employees” over me. how abandoned i felt. .

i suppose one of the lessons is you probably should not go to work with an ex. another is, i was right all along. 
#believeinyourself
#metoo

text:
on the last morning of the retreat, i woke up at 5am and wrote a song on the house guitar... since soulshine bali is home to @micheal_franti - i suspect it’s not the first song that’s been written in this gorgeous yoga chalet — when i get back to sf i’ll record it and share... but for now - here are the lyrics *****************
the feminine soul

we don’t need to be quiet, we don’t need to be calm
don’t need to figure out how to be tough and strong

we don’t need to be taught, we don’t need to be told
tired of fitting into these stupid molds

the fight has been fought, and we’ve already won
the new consciousness has already come

we must shine our lights, fly our flags on the poles
it’s time to reclaim… the feminine soul 
_________________

whatever your gender, whatever your creed
the gifts you have are the gifts we need
don’t buy into the fear that gets spread 
the old consciousness is close to dead
like a pussing wound, or the rattle of a lung
the patriarch knows it’s nearly done 
whether or not they’ve got a conscious clue
every single soul is saying #metoo

chorus

take an inhale, then take an exhale too
there’s nothing that you’re not connected to
the time is up for agreeing to the lies
that fragment us off and polarize
if it’s in him than it’s in me as well
and until it’s loved, it continues to swell
so i’ll look at my shadow, right in her eyes
until her light can’t be denied 
chorus

the mother, the whore, the healer, the crone
are all on the line, if we pick up the phone
unconditioned and back in the wild 
each of us is an innocent child 
if you keep on hating and reacting
your body and soul will keep contracting 
before mama earth says our time is gone
stand together in love and share your song 
chorus 
#soulpoweredwoman #fiercefeminineandfree #soulorientedsomatics #soulshinebali #stayhuman #soulrocker

text:
national | #metoo allegation: anu malik quits ‘indian idol’

details:after the sexual harassment allegations against music composer anu malik, sony entertainment television released an official statement saying , “anu mallik is no longer a part of the indian idol jury panel. the show will continue according to its planned schedule and we will invite some of the biggest names in indian music as guests to join vishal dadlani and neha kakkar to judge the extraordinary talent of indian idol season 10”. following the #metoo movement, anu malik was recently accused of sexual harassment by shweta pandit and sona mohapatra following which two more survivors opened up on their horrific experiences with the bollywood singer.

the movement gained momentum in india after bollywood actor tanushree dutta accused nata patekar of allegedly misbehaving with her during a film shoot in 2008.

#indianidol10 #anumalik #metoocontroversy #metoo #indianidol  #pratidintime

text:
' we wonder what the world will look like if we were less concerned about people receiving judgment and more concerned about people receiving redemption '. when we use the word #metoo , first picture which comes to our mind is of women's safety. initially in the 1920s, women were asking for the most fundamental and advanced right that one can have as a citizen of a democratic country, the right to vote. now almost  100 years later, women today are asking to be safe and to be protected from harassment and violation. that's a huge devolution of all time.

there are lakhs of people who still think that these victims are cooking up stories to gain fame and they are skeptical in believing them.
when it is said #believewomen that doesn't mean that women are inherently more honest than men or that they're somehow better, it just simply mean that she is extremely likely telling the truth because it happens all the time. 1 out of every 3 women is sexually assaulted.
for instance if someone says that pollution in delhi has gone up it is easy to believe as there is nothing new in it and it happens all the time.
there is a huge incentive for women not to come forward because when they do, the consequences are terrible. they are targeted, faces constant harassment and death threats coming from accused, have to go through legal proceedings by hiring an attorney and if they are proved guilty, then all the most vile and hateful names imaginable come their way. 
so it ought to be obvious why these sexual misconduct claims are just not some ploy to bring men down. if someone says a thing happened and it happens all the time, they have everything to lose by coming forward and little to gain. we should take these claims seriously and this is our problem to solve. talk to your friends, tell them you believe women, why you believe them and why we all must believe them.
 #letthatbethenewlockerroomtalk!

text:
#day293 #365daysofyogawithalisa 
no yoga practice. my body needed rest. i slept in and read a 500 page book instead. yes in one day. @angiethomas #thehateugive really opened my mind and broke my heart too

police brutality and #blacklivesmatter has been something i've struggled following online since i first noticed it. now i realize it's because i didn't understand.

i hate when people play victim or innocent about things.

for the longest time i realized i was taking the side of the cops by default because i believe in their integrity. i couldn't fathom why someone of authority would be lying or a criminal. now i realize how stupidly blind and naive that is.

i also got sick of listening to my black friends victimize themselves because their ancestors endured slavery 200 years ago yet they're living richer than i am as a first generation european. it made me lose respect about their "issues". all that nonsense to the side, wow. police do lie. definitely bad cops out there and even moreso, black victims exist. innocent young men and women who die because a cop decides it to be so. and no one gets in trouble for it.

all of that aside, i noticed a similar epidemic with my friendships. you make plans to hang out with someone. concrete, specific ones. like " i'm meeting you here. at this time. with these people. i'll see you tonight. "

and then, the people decide they feel like doing something else. 30 minutes before you are supposed to meet.

what on earth is wrong with my generation? who taught you that it's okay and acceptable to not show up? to do something else that sounds better than your word to your friend?

accountability. a word all of us need to master in our lives. if we say we are gonna do something, we sure as hell better. if something matters to us, we better f*cking show it then.

when you screw something up or hurt me, then best believe i'm going to tell you. and then you better own up to it.

i make the mistake often of thinking others think and act the way i do. you don't. but it's not okay to ditch people. to abandon them.

it's not ok to shoot innocent black teenagers. ever. #yoga #headstand #think #instayoga

text: i have been resistant to commenting too much about the #metoo movement...because as much as i agree with it as a human being whole heartedly,  i also follow quite a few different social causes and have strong passions about those too. i feel passionate about misssing and murdered indigenous women, domestic and sexual violence, child protection from sexual and other abuse, mental health and equality for women . they are in effect along the same lines. how do you feel?  how has the #metoo conversations affected you personally? what are your girlfriends and family talking about?  what about talking with your children? here is my problem...i think me too is extrememly important for so many reasons, mostly because crimes are being perpetrated upon girls and women and there are no consequences for it. also, the long term pain and suffering surviors feel are life long and debilitating. what i think about #metoo, is that is going to have to include enlightened men, justice system reform and a shift in the perception of women as a whole. why?  because if men are are allowed to assault, harass, kill, maim, rape and mistreat women, how will we ever achieve anything that looks like equality?  how can we both empower women and girl without this piece, this huge piece being not only addressed but rectified?  another issue for me, is that there is so much being left out of #metoo for survivors of incest, child sexual abuse and rape...i mean it is kind of being addressed by heightening awareness of the magnitued of abuse, but no one that has suffered terrible things should feel pressured to *reveal their traumas* or be *forced to name their abuser* unless they are ready and unless they have strong supports, perhaps of a therapist and others, and *if* they have a desire to. not everyone has those three things in hand, and to pressure or to force people to do this, and to implicate they are *not brave* are plain wrong, misguided and in my opinion re-traumatizing persons all ready suffering. not cool.  what are your thoughts? #metoo #mmiw #survivorsofsexualabuse #domesticviolence #mentalhealthawareness  #hardconversationsmustbehad
name: Tatiana Shore

text:
senator kirsten gillibrand (d-ny) has legislatively represented new york on the national stage since the mid-2000s. starting as representative of the 20th district, she was then appointed to fill hillary clinton’s senate seat in january 2009 when clinton was asked to be obama’s secretary of state. .
.
as her legal career flourished, gillibrand became further involved with state and national politics with activities with the dnc, going on to win two terms as a representative, and then on to her senate position, winning special election to serve the remainder of clinton’s term in 2010.  the ny senator then would go on to winning re-election in her own right in 2012 at 72%: the largest winning margin for any statewide candidate in new york history, carrying all but just two counties. .
.
during her tenure as senator, gillibrand’s views have shifted to more liberal-minded views, with keen emphasis on advocacy for human rights: speaking out over social issues of sexual assault, and more specifically sexual assault in the military and combating pervasive sexual harassment.  furthermore, gillibrand is continually praised as being the very first member of congress to publish her meeting schedules, with listing each visitor and what they discussed on a given day- fostering the major necessity for transparency in federal government. .
.
during the current administration, gillibrand has been no stranger to being a fierce, articulate critic of donald trump, while continuing to represent new york as a senator, but also for women’s issues and gay-rights for the entire nation. is sen. gillibrand contemplating a run in 2020? she has responded “no,” insisting she is focused on winning 2018 senatorial re-election… but we will see, especially after november 6th; #vote! .
.

text:
lord, use my story for your glory!  i will continue to use my voice every opportunity i get. my story of survival will be someone else's saving grace. 
sharing your story is not an easy thing to do but the best feeling in the world is knowing that you're helping others heal through the transparency in your testimony. never judge a book by its cover,  you never know the pain that a person has had to endure. this is a season where people are in need of being surrounded by love pressure,  there is enough pain in the world and the enemy is looking for who he can devour. be a solution to the problem not salt to wounds. check the spirit you are operating from and begin on your own healing so god can get the full glory.

god placed it in my heart early last year (2017) to write my book "my costa rican humming bird sings breaking the bondage and answering the call" (currently available on amazon) for such a time as this. depression, isolation and suicidal thoughts are a real thing in all nationalities and ethnic backgrounds.  it is time to take the shame off of these topics and begin addressing the monster currently affecting our nation today. 
it is an honor to serve as ambassador for naasca. abuse cycles, depression and mental health are real issues that need to be addressed and supported.

here is my interview where i shared my real story about my sexual abuse on naasca:

http://www.blogtalkradio.com/naasca/2018/10/18/stop-child-abuse-now-scan--1988

isaiah 54:17
no weapon that is formed against thee shall prosper; and every tongue that shall rise against thee in judgment thou shalt condemn. this is the heritage of the servants of the lord, and their righteousness is of me, saith the lord.

job 23:10 "but he knows where i am going. and when he tests me, i will come out as pure as gold.

text_retweet: repost from @lmgfineart using @repostregramapp - censorship is all around us, from social media to television to academia to government institutions. what is hidden and blocked from view reveals the cultural norms that override expression and - subsequently - artists' efforts to contest such norms. alison stinely's art was censored before finding a place at the linda matney art gallery. women artists, like stinely, have had their ideas blocked by institutions for centuries. how does her experience with censorship fit within the era of the #metoo movement? what does the silencing of female expression in today's culture mean for women? alison stinely, diana blanchard gross, vittorio colaizzi, lita tirak and john lee matney held a rigorous panel discussion at the linda matney art gallery on saturday, may 19th 2018"...[stinely] and her proxies refuse to be labeled, restricted, or contained and possess an otherworldly strength beyond the surface of shiny broken fragments." -dr. margaret richardson. director@lindamatneygallery.com  #williamsburgva  tnewportnewsva #norfolkva #odu #artcollection  #757art #richmondva #erie  #malenude #figurativepainting #maleandfemale #3dprinting #florence  #mixedmedia #rva #artmuseum #acrylicpainting #investmentart #censored #sculpture #gilded #popsurrealism #oilpainting #femaleartist #paintings #artist #narrativeart

text:
9.
. .خبر متاخر .
#ساجد_خان يتنحى عن اخراج #هوسفول_4؛ بسبب اتهامه في حملة #مي_تو . .
.
.

أعلن المخرج ساجد خان ، الذي اتهم بالتحرش من قبل ثلاث نساء ، انسحابه من إخراج هوسفول 4، ويأتي هذا في أعقاب مزاعم اتهام  مساعدته السابقه سالوني شوبرا ضده بعد ادعاءات سوء السلوك الجنسي . شارك ساجد خان يوم الجمعة 12 أكتوبر في تغريدة على حسابه بموقع التواصل الاجتماعي تويتر ، قائلا إنه سيتنحى عن منصبه كمخرج هوسفول 4. وتقول رسالته: “يجب أن أبادر بالمسؤولية الأخلاقية عن التنحي عن منصبي القيادي”.
ويقول في بيانه: “في أعقاب الادعاءات ضدي والضغط الذي يجري على عائلتي ، والمنتج ونجوم فيلم هوسفول 4، كان لا بد لي من اتخاذ المسؤولية الأخلاقية ليتنحى عن الإخراج ، حتى الوقت الذي يمكن نفي تلك الدعاوي وإثبات الحقيقة. أطلب من أصدقائي في وسائل الإعلام التكرم بعدم تمرير الحكم حتى ظهور الحقيقة”. وكان النجم اكشاي كومار (بطل العمل) قد طلب بالفعل من منتجي الفيلم إلغاء جميع التعاقدات حتى إجراء مزيد من التحقيقات.
وفي التفاصيل، ووسط ادعاءات التحرش الجنسي التي قدمتها مساعدة مخرج،
كومار، الممثل الرئيسي قد طلب بالفعل من المنتجين للفيلم إلغاء التصوير، وكان أكشاي قد شارك يوم الجمعة 12 أكتوبر تغريدة أيضا على موقع تويتر ، قائلا انه “لن يعمل مع أي مجرمين ثبتت جرائمهم وأنه يجب الاستماع إلى الجميع ومنحهم العدالة التي يستحقونها”
كذلك نشرت توينكل كهنا أيضا في وسائل تواصل الاجتماعية لمشاركتها استياءها على الأحداث الجارية. أقرأ تغريدة "توينكل" ، "سمعت أحداث مروعة من حوادث التحرش ، ومن المروع حقًا أن نسمع ما مرت به هؤلاء النساء. كل من يشارك في هوسفول يحتاج إلى اتخاذ موقف حازم من هذه القضية. هذا لا يمكن أن يستمر. "
الجدير بالذكر أن فيلم هوسفول 4 الذي كان من المقرر عرضه في عيد ديوالي 2019، يضم أيضا النجم نانا باتيكار ، الذي المتهم بالتحرش الجنسي بالفنانة تانوشري دوتا. . . . . .

साजिद खान हाउसफुल 4 के निदेशक के रूप में नीचे कदम; मुझे बहुत प्रभाव है .
. . . 
#sajidkhan steps down as director of #housefull4; #metoo effect .
. . . .
.

stop_filter_tweet: 9. . .خبر متاخر . يتنحى عن اخراج بسبب اتهامه في حملة . . . . أعلن المخرج ساجد خان ، الذي اتهم بالتحرش من قبل ثلاث نساء ، انسحابه من إخراج هوسفول 4، ويأتي هذا في أعقاب مزاعم اتهام مساعدته السابقه سالوني شوبرا ضده بعد ادعاءات سوء السلوك الجنسي . شارك ساجد خان يوم الجمعة 12 أكتوبر في تغريدة على حسابه بموقع التواصل الاجتماعي تويتر ، قائلا إنه سيتنحى عن منصبه كمخرج هوسفول 4 . وتقول رسالته : “ يجب أن أبادر بالمسؤولية الأخلاقية عن التنحي عن منصبي القيادي ” . ويقول في بيانه : “ في أعقاب الادعاءات ضدي والضغط الذي يجري على عائلتي ، والمنتج ونجوم فيلم هوسفول 4، كان لا بد لي من اتخاذ المسؤولية الأخلاقية ليتنحى عن الإخراج ، حتى الوقت الذي يمكن نفي تلك الدعاوي وإثبات الحقيقة . أطلب من أصدقائي في وسائل الإعلام التكرم بعدم تمرير الحكم حتى ظهور الحقيقة ” . وكان النجم اكشاي كومار ( بطل العمل ) قد طلب بالفعل من منتجي الفيلم إلغاء جميع التعاقدات حتى إجراء مزيد من التحقيقات . وفي التفاصيل، ووسط ادعاءات التحرش الجنسي التي قدمتها مساعدة مخرج، كومار، الممثل الرئيسي قد طلب بالفعل من المنتجين للفيلم إلغاء التصوير، وكان أكشاي قد شارك يوم الجمعة 12 أكتوبر تغريدة أيضا على موقع تويتر ، قائلا انه “ لن يعمل مع أي مجرمين ثبتت جرائمهم وأنه يجب الاستماع إلى الجميع ومنحهم العدالة التي يستحقونها ” كذلك نشرت توينكل كهنا أيضا في وسائل تواصل الاجتماعية لمشاركتها استياءها على الأحداث الجارية . أقرأ تغريدة `` توينكل '' ، `` سمعت أحداث مروعة من حوادث التحرش ، ومن المروع حقًا أن نسمع ما مرت به هؤلاء النساء . كل من يشارك في هوسفول يحتاج إلى اتخاذ موقف حازم من هذه القضية . هذا لا يمكن أن يستمر. `` الجدير بالذكر أن فيلم هوسفول 4 الذي كان من المقرر عرضه في عيد ديوالي 2019، يضم أيضا النجم نانا باتيكار ، الذي المتهم بالتحرش الجنسي بالفنانة تانوشري دوتا . . . . . . साजिद खान हाउसफुल 4 के निदेशक के रूप में नीचे कदम ; मुझे बहुत प्रभाव है . . . . steps director effect . . . . . . ollywoodactoractress ewsbollywood

text:
i will dedicate my sunday posts to encourage every man and woman out there who feels helpless by what is happening to our society today.⠀
⠀
the #metoo movement has been a monumental undertaking for all females worldwide and it has given women everywhere a chance to speak out, be heard and be empowered. to quote the spiderman movie, “with great power comes great responsibility.” our society today has inequality written all over it—so what can you do about it?⠀
⠀
power should not be possessed by an individual, even a gender alone. for generations dating back to more than a millenia, patriarchy has ruled our world. now women have been given a right to vote, for free speech, to be educated, for free will. but power shouldn’t be confined to gender. power is within the free will that we have been given. ⠀
⠀
power should be driven by our moral compass. it should be used for the betterment of society and not to be lorded over someone. everyone has the power to be whoever they want to be and to do whatever they want; but if you abuse that power, that’s where inequality sets in. ⠀
⠀
we are all led to believe that feminism is about girl power—it shouldn’t be. it should be more than that. we should all speak up for the power that everyone possesses. to be a voice of freedom for everyone—no matter the gender, race, age or status. power shouldn’t discriminate.⠀
⠀
love for others should be the driving force behind every movement. if it’s not, would it be worth fighting for?⠀ ⠀
tag someone who needs your power of words today. let them know that you are there for them and that you’ll help them any way that you can.⠀
.⠀

// in light of all the darkness that taints the human spirit in the current climate. 
and everything essential, that is the #metoo movement.
.

have these uncomfortable conversations.
with your parents.
with all the men in your life.
with all the women.
start here.

enlighten people around you and believe the survivors when they share their stories.
it takes immense courage and strength to speak up about dark experiences that have left psychological, emotional, and physical scars.
we are fighting our deepest fears and harshest realities.
let us fight them together.

be this change. be there for one another.
listen to these voices. they are pained and you can empower them by believing, listening, and becoming the movement.
@metoomvmt @metoo_in @timesupnow

text:
for as long as i can remember, i have loved to swear. i loved the impact it had and how it could effortlessly emphasize your point. and for as long as i can remember, i have been told to stop doing it. "vulgar" is a word that has been used to describe me on many occasions. boys have told me that swearing makes me less attractive. teachers have told me that it's not ladylike and yet, i continue to swear. i have a particular love for the c-word. the weight of it, the harsh c and t sounds, the versatility....it's perfect. i remember saying the word "cunt" for the first time to describe my middle school teacher, who was particularly terrible. my friends at the time used profanities to articulate all of their sentences but my use of this particular word led them to call me "fucking gross." one of the girls said that her mum had never said that word and would never allow her to say it and i shouldn't either. i knew the word was off limits in my house. i was taught that the c-word was the worst thing that could possibly come out of your mouth and i knew that my mum especially would kill me if she heard me using it. but still, i did and i do...just not in front of her. there is something about the word that is so bold and strong and all encompassing that when used sparingly is so unbelievably effective. maybe it's because i'm british and it is used so much more here or perhaps it's because i'm just the foul mouthed bitch i've been told that i am. either way the word "cunt" will be cherished and in my vocabulary for many years to come. - @kiera_whit .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
excerpts from “groping for truth”. 1/2 ... "gradually, i instinctively discerned that i was not mother’s most favourite child. i was aware i looked ugly in comparison to my sisters and behaved differently from my siblings, but i was too young to understand if the exclusion was due to my dark pigmentation, my skinny body, my almond-shaped eyes with double eyelids or because i always operated at a hyper level.

the physical punishments inflicted by mother escalated from isolation in the corner of our dining room in el tigre, to whippings on my tiny legs with my own black nylon belt i wore over my white school uniform in san fernando.

mother would hold me by the left arm and strike me until red blotches swelled up on my legs like purple dragon tree leaves. my sisters would then tease me by singing in spanish, “le florecieron!” which meant, her flowers had blossomed.

this new type of punishment was psychologically tougher than being secluded in a dark corner because it left distinctive marks visible to everybody at home and at school. so not only was it physically painful, but it also produced emotional wounds that would bleed on my memory’s walls for years to come.

the day i hit my brother on the head, i remained alert, expecting mother to come for me to draw more purple leaves on the back of my legs. hours later when i had almost forgotten about it, mother emerged from the kitchen carrying the black nylon belt. my sisters’ murmurs alerted me, i jumped off the sofa where i was sitting in the family room and started running around the house. mother ran after me. we were dashing about and squealing like two wild boars, from the bedroom to the kitchen and across the hall to the dining room.

the six-seater rectangular, wooden table, covered with a colourfully embroidered, white table cloth, occupied most of the space in the middle of the dining room. i spun left and right around the table while mother tried to catch me, again yelling, “inagsek ala umrik!” and “badi idbahik!” i will kill you!

text_retweet: repost from @lmgfineart using @repostregramapp - censorship is all around us, from social media to television to academia to government institutions. what is hidden and blocked from view reveals the cultural norms that override expression and - subsequently - artists' efforts to contest such norms. alison stinely's art was censored before finding a place at the linda matney art gallery. women artists, like stinely, have had their ideas blocked by institutions for centuries. how does her experience with censorship fit within the era of the #metoo movement? what does the silencing of female expression in today's culture mean for women? alison stinely, diana blanchard gross, vittorio colaizzi, lita tirak and john lee matney held a rigorous panel discussion at the linda matney art gallery on saturday, may 19th 2018"...[stinely] and her proxies refuse to be labeled, restricted, or contained and possess an otherworldly strength beyond the surface of shiny broken fragments." -dr. margaret richardson. director@lindamatneygallery.com  #williamsburgva  tnewportnewsva #norfolkva #odu #artcollection  #757art #richmondva #erie  #malenude #figurativepainting #maleandfemale #3dprinting #florence  #mixedmedia #rva #artmuseum #acrylicpainting #investmentart #censored #sculpture #gilded #popsurrealism #oilpainting #femaleartist #paintings #artist #narrativeart

text:
excerpts from "groping for truth" 2/2 ..."the punch was so robust, half the orderly-placed glasses and china dishes went cascading down and crashed on the polished concrete floor. mother could not believe her eyes. neither could i. i took advantage of the distraction and fled the dining room. 
i sprinted across the back yard, scattering the hens and rooster pecking around the yard, until i reached the pond where our two pet ducks swam peacefully. i took a seat on the tarnished old barrel turned on its side against the red block fence that separated our back yard from the outside world. the rusted barrel served as a hatching nest for the hens and sleeping area for the ducks. it took me several minutes to calm down as i gulped and gasped to catch my breath. 
distressed and apprehensive, i could not comprehend then that my aggressive and destructive behaviour, particularly towards mother, was an unconscious response to years of psychological abuse and physical punishment inflicted upon me." #metoo #bookstagram #book #metoomovement #newbook #colorfulmontaha #colorlanding #bookworm #bookwriter #author #authorsofinstagram #gropingfortruth #abuse #abusesurvivor #enoughisenough

join the movement! join us in our campaign to end indonesia’s dog and cat meat trade!

every year, hundreds of thousands of dogs and cats are slaughtered for human consumption in indonesia – their suffering is unimaginable…

but it doesn’t have to be this way!

the animal rights movement is growing in indonesia and as a founding member of the dog meat free indonesia coalition, change for animals foundation is committed to ending this horror!

but we need your help! please…

1- sign & share the petition here: www.dogmeatfreeindonesia.org/take-action

2- find out more about the campaign and consider making a donation to support us: www.changeforanimals.org/ending-the-dog-meat-trade-indonesia

3- help us raise awareness an support by sharing this post

text:
with the #metoo campaign currently on its 1st anniversary, i feel like i need to share something. if you are a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, there is something you can do to help you on your journey to heal. and it is open to anyone worldwide. 
the younique foundation offers a free retreat to survivors of childhood sexual abuse. they don't force younique products on you, they don't even use our products in the makeover and photoshoot because they don't want there to be even an ounce of room for someone to say they have the wrong intentions. this foundation has one purpose, and one purpose only: to help you heal. 
no business. no sales. nothing except opportunities for you to rediscover your self-worth and heal. you are powerful beyond measure. 
if you want to know more, please check out www.youniquefoundation.org, where you can read more and apply to attend the retreat or contact me. 
#nomore1in4 #reclaimhope  #ibelieveyou #theyouniquefoundation
