text:
'judith beheading holofernes' by artemisia gentileschi, c. 1620-1

artemisia was a baroque painter of the medici court whose artistic achievements were overshadowed by a successful yet prolonged rape trial against senior painter, agostino tassi.  while the biblical story of judith killing holofernes has been represented by a number of (male) painters, artemisia's version is truly filled with audacious details of rage, determination and female solidarity. i could almost feel her anger towards tassi as i looked at this painting for a while.

text:
#metoo 
women of mythology too!
.
.
since it's my third day of posting about decoding raavan, i might as well go all the way and make it to a ten! #saywhat 🤔
anyway, this 📷 was compelling enough to share, even though i do not know the cartoonist -- in addition to punning on the evil in our society -- it's clear as day to me, that a movement or revolution is never limited by time in human years. 📡📆
if we are in kalyuga or the iron age, as i believe we are -- and if history is repeating itself every yuga (averaging a half a million years), i wonder if racism, sexism, hedonism, genocide etc. is playing out right now exactly the way it did then - same colour, same intensity, same degree, same same.
🕯
and if so, can even a micro shift in the time-space continuum greatly alter the 'replay code' for the next million years or so?
🔌
do we know how to make that shift? which levers to move or buttons to press? is our collective fire of revolution capable of exhuming the demons for good?
.
excerpts from the book, heroines:
draupadi -- the lotus-eyed, dark-skinned dharma queen, whose story emerges almost three millennia ago. she too, is humiliated in an all-male assembly -- a queen bartered as a pawn in a game of gamble. she is abandoned, which earns her the terrible descriptor of 'nathavati anathavat' --- husbanded, yet unprotected. she stood for herself, courageous, righteous and questioning, and makes a declaration which is part malediction part promise "i shall never forgive the kauravas for doing what they did to me. i shall not tie my hair until i wash it in dusshasana's blood." the mahabharata repeatedly throws up the issue of the ownership of the fertility of women. 
unlike sita, draupadi physically defends herself each time she is assaulted. .
yet intriguingly, young girls are still named parvati, sita, radha, meera - never draupadi. 🤐
does it say something about us as a race? does a #metoo have to happen to shake humankind to its core so we can wake up to choosing our heroes or heroines rightly?
🙋🏻
since this goes as my #day41 post, i'd love to hear any artists' experiences & expressions of mythological women in today's context 😇
#100daysofart
name: Arteree (pronounced Artery)
tweet_full:
#metoo 
women of mythology too!
.
.
since it is my third day of posting about decoding raavan, i might as well go all the way and make it to a ten! #saywhat 🤔
anyway, this 📷 was compelling enough to share, even though i do not know the cartoonist -- in addition to punning on the evil in our society -- it is clear as day to me, that a movement or revolution is never limited by time in human years. 📡📆
if we are in kalyuga or the iron age, as i believe we are -- and if history is repeating itself every yuga (averaging a half a million years), i wonder if racism, sexism, hedonism, genocide etc. is playing out right now exactly the way it did then - same colour, same intensity, same degree, same same.
🕯
and if so, can even a micro shift in the time-space continuum greatly alter the 'replay code' for the next million years or so?
🔌
do we know how to make that shift? which levers to move or buttons to press? is our collective fire of revolution capable of exhuming the demons for good?

text:
dear good guys,
the silence from you is being noticed. 
bro code, bromance, bros before hoes - and all the other fragile walls of bro-fence you're hiding behind is being noticed. you saw, you knew, you know. why this silence then? you never missed an opportunity to share your entitled opinions before. 
because, how could you fail a bro? it's his "private matter", better not to be involved? society never taught you men to talk about personal responsibilities in the first place? which excuse are we going with today, #deargoodguys?
you are better than this. we are better than this. we can do better than this. 
let's talk.
-opashona ghosh @opashona .

text:
det är inget nytt att män reser till thailand (och andra länder runtom i asien) för att köpa sex.
för att ha kul på en annan människas bekostnad.
många verkar anse att de gör dessa kvinnor (och barn) en tjänst, att de hjälper deras ekonomi genom att betala dem för sexuella tjänster.
andra försöker urskulda sig genom att påstå att de är annan kultur än sverige och de följer bara seden i landet de besöker.
vi kan nog alla hålla med om att dessa kvinnor och barn inte anser  männen göra dem en tjänst när de köper sexuella tjänster av dem.
detta är det eviga sättet att fortsätta reproducera bilden av att de flesta asiatiska kvinnor och icke-män endast är till för sexuell njutning, att de är undergivna hemmafruar/sexdockor.
en bild som måste sluta reproduceras, och sexturism är en problematiskt turism som måste upphöra!
länk till artikel: https://arbetet.se/2018/10/18/sa-sexturistar-svenska-man-i-thailand/

text:
privileged to be a part of #261 vision toastmasters at st. mary's college in yousufguda. 
humbled to receive this token of gratitude from dr. prasad who was the tmod at vision toastmasters today.
.
i was a key-note speaker all thanks to adarsh who was my reader at the human library event a few months back.
.
upon his recommendation, i was invited as a key-note speaker at the toastmasters event today and the theme was #metoo.
.
well i simply shared my story, "resilience - bouncing back with strength", which i do at human library hyderabad as well.
a sunday morning well spent. looking forward to more such meetups! 😍
. .

text: historians refer to the abolition of #sati as the first watershed moment in india’s modern feminist movement. this led to the first wave of #feminisminindia.  a lot of the early struggle saw educated middle class men such as raja ram mohan roy (who crusaded against social evils like sati, polygamy and child marriage), ishwar chandra vidyasagar (who championed the cause of widow remarriage) and dd #karve ( who worked towards eradicating the bias against widows) take a feminist stand. several indian states were ruled by women during british colonial advance including jhansi (rani laxmibai), kittur (rani chennama), bhopal (quidisa begum) and punjab (jind kaur). #unfoundmasterclass #metoo

text:
actor ayushmann khurrana has supported the #metoo movement by saying that men should understand what consent is.

ayushmann visited the pvr citi mall here on saturday to know the audience's reaction for his latest film "badhaai ho". reacting to the #metoo campaign that has gathered momentum in india, especially in bollywood, ayushmann told media: "the #metoo movement is a good movement, but at the same time, i feel both parties should be given equal opportunities to share their account and to prove their innocence. having said that, i feel women should be respected and they shouldn't be harassed. "there should be stringent rules at every workplace. it is not only about workplace, but i think that the code of conduct should be followed in every sphere of society, be it our family or where we live."

text:
"그게 말이지. 아픈 사람을 알아보는 건, 더 아픈 사람이란다...."
.
아픈 사람들은 서로 알아본다.
서로가 겪은 끔찍함을 알기 때문에 서로 챙기고 위로하고 연대한다.
아픔에 공감하는 사람과 함께하고 싶어서 일부러 찾아 나서기도 한다.
하지만 아픈 사람의 상처를 들추려 하는 것은 잔인한 행동이다.
.
며칠 전 로스쿨 친구들과 술을 마시다가 a반의 어떤 남학생이 sns에 올린 짤을 같이 봤다. (나는 b반이다.)
"형법수업 중간고사에게 강간당했는데 이제 강간에 대해서 배워야 되네" 라는 내용이었다.
미국에서는 흔히 학생들이 어려운 시험을 보고 난 뒤 강간당했다는 표현을 쓴다.
참 끔찍한 단어를 너무 쉽고 부적절하게 사용한다.
(나도 어렸을때 아무 생각 없이 그랬었다.)
그 학생의 짤에 내가 아는 a반 여학생이 댓글을 달았다.
"혹시라도 이 짤이 성폭행 당한 학생의 상처를 더 아프게 할 수 있으니까 앞으로는 강간이라는 단어를 그런 식으로 쓰지 말아 달라"는 내용이었다.
.
남자들은 대부분 모른다.
성폭행이나 성희롱은 주로 여자들이 겪는 거니까.
그 여학생도 상처를 겪어 봤기 때문에 비슷한 상처가 있을지도 모르는 학생들을 위해 나선 게 아닐까?
댓글을 본 내 친구들은 다 그 여학생을 칭찬했고 남학생을 무식하다고 욕했다.
글을 같이 본 다른 a반 남학생도 동의했다.
그리고는 갑자기 자신의 삼촌이 강간범을 변호해서 법원에서 승리한 사례를 불필요한 디테일까지 포함해서 들려줬다.
방금 학생들 중에 성폭행이나 성희롱 피해자가 있을지도 모르니 조심하자는 대화를 했음에도 불구하고 말이다.
그런 상처를 겪어본 적도 없고 겪을 수도 있다는 생각을 하지 않기 때문에 가능한 것일지도 모른다.
아니면 그냥 생각이 없을지도.
.
me too 운동도 상처의 끔찍함을 겪어본 사람들의 연대다.
me too를 비판하는 사람은 그 상처를 모르기 때문에 아픈 사람들한테 왜 징징대냐고 짜증낸다.
상처를 겪은 사람들이 상처의 원인을 없애는 방법을 말하고 있다.
그들의 목소리에 귀기울이고 다른 사람들을 아프지 않게 하는 게 옳지 않은가?
.
.
.
#언어의온도 #이기주 #더아픈사람 #페미니즘 #페미니스트 #로스쿨 #미투 #metoo #상처에대하여 #새벽독서
name: Sophie Paeng

( 나도 어렸을때 아무 생각 없이 그랬었다 . ) 그 학생의 짤에 내가 아는 a반 여학생이 댓글을 달았다 . `` 혹시라도 이 짤이 성폭행 당한 학생의 상처를 더 아프게 할 수 있으니까 앞으로는 강간이라는 단어를 그런 식으로 쓰지 말아 달라 '' 는 내용이었다 . . 남자들은 대부분 모른다 . 성폭행이나 성희롱은 주로 여자들이 겪는 거니까 . 그 여학생도 상처를 겪어 봤기 때문에 비슷한 상처가 있을지도 모르는 학생들을 위해 나선 게 아닐까 ? 댓글을 본 내 친구들은 다 그 여학생을 칭찬했고 남학생을 무식하다고 욕했다 . 글을 같이 본 다른 a반 남학생도 동의했다 . 그리고는 갑자기 자신의 삼촌이 강간범을 변호해서 법원에서 승리한 사례를 불필요한 디테일까지 포함해서 들려줬다 . 방금 학생들 중에 성폭행이나 성희롱 피해자가 있을지도 모르니 조심하자는 대화를 했음에도 불구하고 말이다 . 그런 상처를 겪어본 적도 없고 겪을 수도 있다는 생각을 하지 않기 때문에 가능한 것일지도 모른다 . 아니면 그냥 생각이 없을지도 . . 운동도 상처의 끔찍함을 겪어본 사람들의 연대다 . too를 비판하는 사람은 그 상처를 모르기 때문에 아픈 사람들한테 왜 징징대냐고 짜증낸다 . 상처를 겪은 사람들이 상처의 원인을 없애는 방법을 말하고 있다 . 그들의 목소리에 귀기울이고 다른 사람들을 아프지 않게 하는 게 옳지 않은가 ? . . .

text:
#metoo ! 
it seems like this #hashtag is back in business and this time around, it's doing the rounds in india! i'm shocked to see my feed full of "me too" posts from so many of my friends, co-workers, acquaintances' experiences that i had no idea about up until now!i'm talking about strong, successful, independent, self-made women from all kinds of fields - entrepreneurs, cxos of big name companies and spiritual circles alike! it's easy to think that a lot of such behavior comes from strangers, but we'd be surprised to know that more often than not, it comes from people we know socially - work wise and otherwise.
truth be told, not a lot of us can say we know people who have never ever been a victim of anything like this! atleast, i can't!
this is from a photo series i created back in 2016-2017. this series was my way of speaking up to express my own personal experience of when i was beaten up, harassed, assaulted, physically+emotionally tortured for over three hours by someone who was not a stranger! i was left on the side of the road with my clothes torn, all my essentials - phone, wallet, vehicle, keys, rain jacket, footwear etc taken away from me and destroyed to make sure i can't seek help quickly on that rainy night in a secluded part of town. it took me an hour and more of running barefoot, shivering and shaking, to get help. 
the authorities instead of helping, resorted to #victimblaming #shaming me for being an independent woman, minimising the extent of damage done to me by telling me that there is no case because there is no rape! 
it seems like that's where they draw the line and any experience short of rape, is non-issue and we as women are over-reacting! 
i really hope this movement picks up momentum this time around, to bring about some fundamental changes to protect our rights. i'm talking about human rights and not just women's rights. 
power to everyone that's speaking up and standing up against this sick epidemic of abuse of power, coz that's the real cause of all kinds of harassment. 
#metooindia
#india #social #change 
#womensrights
#storiesofindia #untoldvisuals #sogoa 
#dd_goa #goatrippers #pickmygoapic #artofvisuals #healing

text:
you can't know where you're going until you know where you've come from. and if you live in a big city like me, you may realise that with all your running, you never move from where you are. honour that place, remember your history.

i had a chance to share one of my most treasured stories on stage. this happened on the same day i crashed under the weight of #metoo. i was naked on stage and in the story of my city. and maybe this is the only way to be. mumbai demands it. 
the video of this piece is up on @indiehabitat facebook page and youtube here: http://youtu.be/gldlpjcdmtg 
welcome to my city. honour the birds and honour the breaking walls.

text:
i create these goddess yoni's for self healing and self expression. the coloring books grew out of a need to share ~ i completely gain the same benefits of practicing meditation when i create / 'do' art, and my sincere wish is that other wimmin might benefit as well. how this all works, this getting gy coloring books to wimmin who can't meditate yet for healing or self care, but can color and get the similar effects, that part i do not know. but like everything else in my life, i am trusting a way will reveal itself. blessed be.

text:
nikal hi rahi thi ghar se zindagi k tajurbe lene,
ki maa ne awaz laga k kaha-
sun! ye zism hi hai gehena tera,
issi se izzat humari tolenge,
agar logo k kaido se nahi chali toh bhare bazar mai tujhe kosenge.
sun k bas aage do kadam hi chali thi,
sunsan si us gali mai sannate ki awaz bhi gunj rahi thi,
dabbe pao chupa tha andhero mai,
fir achanak samne aaya,
uski gandi nazaro ne mujhe nazaro hi ganda kar dala.

na baal hai mere itne ghane na 
dupatte ka rang itna gehera ki sharir mai khud ka chupa saku,
uski aankhon main hai hawas itna na burkha na saree pehen k khud ko bacha saku.
mitti se maile ye daag, pani se bhi na mita saku.

har mod har galli mai tujh jaise hazar mile,
har kisi k zubaan par bas mere hi zism k charche sune.
lot k jo ghar aai toh maa bhi boli-
ye haiwano ka hai zamana, chetavani bhi tujhe di thi,
logo k taane kaise ab tu sunenge.
ab kankar mitti se humari izzat tolenge.
jo ab tak kabhi kuch na bola, vo bhi humme bolenge.
bhul jaa aisa bhi kabhi hua tha,
yeh log bhi sab bhul jaenge.
jo tune awaz uthaya, toh log bhi tamasha banaenge.
us haiwan ko sab ki nazaro mai acha aur tujhe kalankit bataenge.
har charche mai tera naam uchalenge, aur fir koi naye kahani apne maan se banaenge.

par maa, 
kya yahi hai zindagi, kya yahi hai is k tajurbe.
kya awaz uthane par mujhe toka jaenga,
kya khilono ki tarha mujhse khela jaenga,
maa, kya aise hi naam mera lia jaenga, 
kya zinda rehene k lie mujhe kossa jaenga.
© effulgence

name: Sandra Jane Silent
tweet_full: #metoo #abused #survivor #iamalive #nosoul #deadinside

text:
"she with one of him"
acrylics on canvas
24x36 inches
.
.
. .abuse is any child’s worst nightmare; physical abuse can wound human soul terribly when it comes with sexual assault. my work is about such experiences which i have lived through every day once when it was happening and now when it has happened. i paint self-portraits as my catharsis, i have tried words earlier but this has served me more than any medium. it’s a cage of my own self which never let me out. it’s not only me; it’s every other person in different prison of inner self hiding others’ mistakes. i have lived through it and will be breathing through it. all that dirt poured on my soul was not mine, how it could be; i was just a child, i was ‘she’. my work is a narration of my emotional struggle being a survivor of sexual abuse mainly. it is a statement about psychological and emotional impact of abuse on children as well as adults. our social taboos does not allow women as well as men to raise a voice about their sufferings which makes it more suffocating. we don't have a way out of this because we don't have any one to listen or understand. .
.

. .abuse is any child’s worst nightmare; physical abuse can wound human soul terribly when it comes with sexual assault. my work is about such experiences which i have lived through every day once when it was happening and now when it has happened. i paint self-poraits as my catharsis, i have tried words earlier but this has served me more than any medium. it’s a cage of my own self which never let me out. it’s not only me; it’s every other person in different prison of inner self hiding others’ mistakes. i have lived through it and will be breathing through it. all that di poured on my soul was not mine, how it could be; i was just a child, i was ‘she’. my work is a narration of my emotional struggle being a survivor of sexual abuse mainly. it is a statement about psychological and emotional impact of abuse on children as well as adults. our social taboos does not allow women as well as men to raise a voice about their sufferings which makes it more suffocating. we do not have a way out of this because we do not have any one to listen or understand. .
.
